  "summary": "Japan's deposit-taking system is not one license. The Banking Act, Trust Business Act, 信用金庫法, 中小企業等協同組合法, 労働金庫法, and 農林中央金庫法 each carve out distinct license tiers with different statutes, regulators, capital floors, deposit-insurance regimes, permitted-activity envelopes, and governance shapes. This",
